be.stevenroose.javastar
Interface Node

All Known Implementing Classes:
TestNode, TestNode
public interface Node

Node classes should extend this abstract class. The reason this class is not an interface is to enforce users to override the equals() and hashCode() methods because the algorithm heavily relies on them.
Using good hashCode values means better performance of the algorithm.
It is advised to make your Node implementation an Immutable Class.

Author:
Steven Roose
